Books are classify and summary first by Field and then by Author.

For the English is not RoamWonder's mother tongue, there will be some uncorrect syntax or vocabulary, I hope you can assist me with Contributing. Thank you...

All the books summary in this "Reading Summary" had been read by RoamWonder. Some are read in English version, but most of them are read in Chinese version.
About this Recommendation
When the book is equal or higher than "Four Stars‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê", RoamWonder thought it will worth you pay some attention to it.

One Star‚≠ê: At any time, it is not recommend you buy or read.
Two Stars‚≠ê‚≠ê: It is not good. En, sometimes may guide you to the wrong way ( be carefully üòü), but if you are rich or have many time to waste, buy or read it.
Three Stars‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê: It is OK. Sometimes, it would be useful.
Four Stars‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê: It is a good book.
Five Stars‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê: Very good, it is strongly recommend you buy or read.
Beyond Five Stars‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠êüåü: If you are working or interesting in the field, you should buy or read it in no doubt. It will higher your level, at least make you look like pompous üòâ.

Contributing
It is very thanks for your contribution if you can correct or add some summary to my reading summary. It will help me and who read this "Reading Summary" so much.
You can following the common github method as follows:

Fork: Fork repository in github https://github.com/RoamWonder/book_reading-summary.
Change: Correct my summary or add your summary following the markdown syntax.
Commit: Commit your change.
Push: Push your change.
Pull Request: Create a "Pull Request".
